Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libgtk-4-1, libcairo2, libpango-1.0-0, libpangocairo-1.0-0, x11-utils
Description: Linux keyboard automation tool with 3x3 hotkey grid
 HotKeys is a Linux port of a Windows keyboard automation tool written in Rust.
 It displays a 3x3 board for quick action selection via numeric keypad keys [1-9],
 designed primarily for software developers but useful for any user preferring
 keyboard over mouse navigation.
 .
 Features:
  - GTK4-based 3x3 hotkey grid interface
  - Application-specific hotkey boards
  - Support for keyboard shortcuts, text input, and automation
  - Profile-based board organization
  - Modifier key combinations for advanced layouts
  - Works on X11 (limited functionality on Wayland)